    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "motion": "fade"
      },
      "narration_text": "Cancer drugs are supposed to kill cancer cells. Here blast counts fall but the cells do not die — they mature. How does blocking a metabolic enzyme produce cells that finish differentiating?",
      "estimated_duration_s": 14.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.07,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "motion": "build"
      },
      "narration_text": "Normal blood development runs one way: a stem cell commits, matures through stages, and dies of old age. The mature cell is the endpoint.",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.01,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "motion": "freeze"
      },
      "narration_text": "In AML, that program stalls. Blasts — immature progenitors — accumulate because the differentiation gate is locked shut.",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.25,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "motion": "build"
      },
      "narration_text": "The IDH1 mutation produces a metabolite called 2-hydroxyglutarate — 2HG. It resembles the molecule demethylases need to erase methyl marks.",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.4,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "motion": "morph"
      },
      "narration_text": "2HG jams the demethylases. Methyl marks that should be erased to open differentiation genes stay in place. The epigenetic lock holds.",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.96,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-differentiation-therapy/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "type": "GRAPHIC",
      "source": "own",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "motion": "morph"
      },
      "narration_text": "Ivosidenib blocks the mutant IDH1 enzyme. 2HG falls. Demethylases recover. The methyl marks on differentiation genes are gradually erased.",
